{{Quote|I can't move it! It's got some sort of density projector!|[[Saesee Tiin/Legends|Saesee Tiin]]|<ref name="Heavy Metal Jedi">{{CWACite|1|Heavy Metal Jedi}}</ref>}}
A '''density projector''' was a device similar to a [[Tractor beam projector/Legends|tractor beam generator]] and was used by the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|CIS]] [[B3 ultra battle droid]]. The projector increased the droid's density, allowing it to effectively anchor itself where it stood. An ultra battle droid with its density projector active was virtually impossible to knock down, even for a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] using [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. However, malfunctions sometimes caused ultra battle droids to be unable to deactivate their density projectors, rendering them easy targets for Republic artillery. This design flaw made it impossible to use the otherwise exceptional droids to full effect, and [[Baktoid Combat Automata/Legends|Baktoid Combat Automata]] was unable to resolve the problem until near the end of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].

